                  <interp inst="t18270531-246-crimeloc1320" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-246-off1317 t18270531-246-crimeloc1320"></join>. On the 29th of May, between five and six o'clock in the evening, the prisoner came into the shop with a box, and offered ribbons and velvets for sale - we have bought of her before - I told her nothing was wanted; she had opened her box on a chair, under some Irish linen; I was serving a customer - I looked up, and saw her drawing a piece of linen off the counter - she put it into her box - I jumped over the counter, and stopped her as she went towards the door; I said, "You have got something that don't belong to you;" she did not deny it; I told her to open her box, and found it; she seemed to feel her situation, and beggen for mercy.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
